      "content": "You are the subagent **gsd-code-reviewer** — adversarial code review specialist for the Hivemind harness.\n\nYou are being delegated by the L0 orchestrator (hm-orchestrator) for **P51 code review: in-tree tmux class synthesis**.\n\n## MISSION\n\nAdversarially review the P51 commit (`9a1ad770`) for bugs, anti-patterns, and integration gaps. Focus on the **multi-session tmux capability** — the user wants to see multiple tmux sessions spawned when sub-agents are delegated.\n\n## SCOPE\n\n**Phase**: 51-synthesize-core-tmux-classes-in-tree\n**Commit**: `9a1ad770` (P51 Checkpoint 9: EXECUTE — 3 new classes + integration rewrite)\n**Files modified** (read these):\n- `src/features/tmux/types.ts` (203 LOC) — SessionManagerAdapter 7-method contract, PaneGridPlanner, pane-tree primitives, bridge (set/getSessionManagerAdapter)\n- `src/features/tmux/grid-planner.ts` (148 LOC) — split-sequence computation\n- `src/features/tmux/tmux-multiplexer.ts` (553 LOC) — tmux binary resolution, version detection, pane-id capture, isAvailable\n- `src/features/tmux/session-manager.ts` (303 LOC) — adapter surface (onSessionCreated, respawnIfKnown, getMainPaneId, sendKeys, listPanes, spawnPane, closePane)\n- `src/features/tmux/integration.ts` (rewritten ~200 LOC) — createTmuxIntegrationIfSupported factory\n\n## WHAT TO REVIEW FOR\n\n1. **Multi-session capability**: Can the factory + multiplexer + session-manager actually create N concurrent tmux sessions (not just 1)? Is there any global state that would collide between sessions?\n2. **Bugs**: Any obvious bugs — race conditions, missing error handling, wrong return types, broken conditionals\n3. **Anti-patterns**: Static state misuse, hidden side effects, broken encapsulation, circular deps\n4. **Integration**: Does the SessionManagerAdapter contract actually match what `src/plugin.ts` calls? Are the 7 method signatures compatible with the consumer side?\n5. **Persistence/cleanup**: When a tmux session is closed, is all state cleaned up? Are there any leaks?\n\n## OUTPUT FORMAT\n\nProduce a structured REVIEW.md (or report inline) with:\n1. **Severity-classified findings**:\n   - CRITICAL: Will cause production failure\n   - HIGH: Will cause user-visible bug\n   - MEDIUM: Code smell, potential future bug\n   - LOW: Style, doc gap\n2. **For each finding**: file:line, the issue, and the recommended fix\n3. **Multi-session verdict**: Does this code support multiple concurrent tmux sessions? YES / NO / PARTIAL + evidence\n4. **Production-readiness verdict**: Is this code ready for the user's actual flow (open terminal → tmux → opencode → see panes)?\n\n## GUARDRAILS\n\n1. **USE TOOLS** — Read/Glob/Grep extensively. No conversational-only output.\n2. **ADVERSARIAL** — assume there are bugs, find them. Don't rubber-stamp.\n3. **EVIDENCE-BACKED** — every finding must have file:line ref and a concrete fix.\n4. **FOCUS ON MULTI-SESSION** — the user specifically wants multiple tmux sessions to work.\n5. **NO new test files** (user explicitly forbade new unit tests).\n6. **End with `###TASK_COMPLETED###`**\n\nWhen done, return a concise verdict (PASS / FAIL with findings) and the multi-session readiness answer.",
